summary: 10/02/1993: Four men and a woman, all in their 20s, were cut by flying glass and suffered shock from the four blasts which the IRA exploded in Finchley Road, North London, shortly before 12.30am.
target1: Civilians on Finchley Road, North London
motive: The attack was perpetrated in an effort to derail peace talks.
scite1: Dirk Beveridge, “Three Bombs Injure 4 in Northwest London, Police Say,” The Associated Press Worldstream, October 1, 1993.
scite2: “Four Injured by Explosions on Busy N. London Road,” Chicago Sun-Times, October 3, 1993.
scite3: “Police Release Picture in Hunt for IRA Bombers,” Press Association, October 3, 1993
